


 THE ZOOKEEPER SERVER IS READY TO START. 
Open the command prompt and go to the kafka_2.12-2.6.0\bin\windows directory. Then, type the command:
zookeeper-server-start.bat ../../config/zookeeper.Properties

 TO START KAFKA-SERVER :-
Open the command prompt and go to the kafka_2.12-2.6.0\bin\windows directory. Then, type the command:
kafka-server-start.bat ../../config/server.properties

 CREATE TOPIC IN KAFKA :-
kafka-topics.bat --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --create --topic mydemo

 TO SEE TOPIC LIST IN KAFKA :-
kafka-topics.bat --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --list

Describing the new topic
kafka-topics.bat --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --describe

Create topic with 3 partitionans
kafka-topics.bat --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --create --topic mydemo --partitions 3 --replication-factor 
